{"cursor":"2203","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox Software\n| name = Beacon Designer logo =\n\n| screenshot = caption = developer = Premier Biosoft latest release version =\n| 7.9 latest release date = 17 June 2010 latest preview version = latest preview\n| date = operating system = Windows, Macintosh platform = genre = Bioinformatics\n| license = commercial website = http://www.premierbiosoft.com\n}} 'Beacon Designer' designs highly specific and efficient primers and probes\nfor real time PCR (polymerase chain reaction) assays. It is compatible to work\non Windows as well as on Mac. The software currently supports the following real\ntime PCR chemistries for efficient primer and probe design.\n\n1. SYBR Green \n2. TaqMan \n3. Molecular beacon \n4. HRMA Primers \n5. Scorpions \n6. FRET \n7. LNA (Locked nucleic acid)\n8. NASBA \n\nBeacon Designer program has built in support for homology avoidance using the\nstandard web BLAST service or the set-up of a desktop BLAST feature for\nidentification of regions that are significantly cross homologous with the\ntarget gene sequence. The software designs real time pcr primers and probes for\ncomplex differential gene expression and allele discrimination assays. Avoidance\nof the cross homology renders specificity to the primers in question and they\nare highly targeted and only amplify the intend sequence and no other targets.\n\nBeacon Designer has been used in workshops and conferences related to real time\nPCR study as a reference software.\n\nThe author company, Premier Biosoft has also launched a simple version for\nevaluation of oligos for real time PCR primers and probes (support limited to\nTaqMan and SYBR Green primers) by the name Beacon designer free version.\n","linknr":105,"url":"Beacon_Designer","recorded":1376427565,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Beacon_designer&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Beacon_designer&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearc